article.headline: SE Louisiana 72, Tex San Antonio 68
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Ricky Woods recorded his eighth double-double of the season, scoring 24 points and grabbing 11 rebounds, as Southeastern Louisiana defeated Texas-San Antonio 72-68 in the Southland Conference opener for both teams Thursday. Quennell Green added 15 points while Terry Bryant had 12 points and six assists as Southeastern (7-5, 1-0 Southland) finished 19-for-20 (95 percent) from the free-throw line. Southeastern made its final 14 attempts at the line, including all 13 in the second half. Andre Owens led the Roadrunners (5-7, 0-1) with 17 points and Roderick Rodgers added 10. Chris Lee sank a pair of free throws, his only points of the night, to push the Lion lead to 68-64 with 19.6 seconds left before Texas-San Antonio's Kyile Byrd sank an apparent 3-pointer with 10.2 seconds left. But officials ruled that Byrd stepped on the line. After being fouled on the ensuing inbounds pass, Bryant drained a pair of free throws with 7.5 seconds left to give Southeastern a 70-66 lead before Aldric Reynolds drove the length of the court and hit a layup that got the Roadrunners to within 70-68 with 1.6 seconds remaining. Woods, who scored 11 points in the second half, was fouled on the Lions' ensuing inbounds pass and made both free throws with 0.8 seconds left that secure the win.
